amdgpu: uvd_v4_2 — extend fw mirror to cover all 3 Sony regions (v76d-β-2-A4)

A3 closed all VM faults (zero fault count) but the VCPU still stalls
at STATUS=0x4 without ever asserting bit 1 (ready). The firmware
executes cleanly with no memory access errors, but never completes
its init handshake.

A4 hypothesis: maybe the firmware silently reads/writes regions 2 and
3 during init and we just don't see the faults because... no wait,
we DO see all faults via the VM_CONTEXT1_PROTECTION_FAULT IH path.
The zero-fault count means region 2/3 aren't being touched.

But that doesn't mean they're not REQUIRED for the firmware's idle
handshake. The fw might be polling a flag in region 3 (message queue
"ready" signal from host) without actually reading the page (e.g., a
register-backed flag). Or it might be waiting for a memory write
from us into region 2 (heap setup).

This patch is the cheap "map everything Sony maps" test:
- Extends the mirror BO from 0x1E0000 (region 1) to 0x308000 (all 3)
- Region 2 (heap/IB, 1168 KB) and region 3 (msgq, 16 KB) initialized
  to zero
- Bind 776 pages (3.1 MB) at GART 0x300000000

If still STATUS=0x4 stall after this, regions aren't the gate, and
we pivot to A5 (instrument bring-up) or A6 (retarget cache offset).

The BO size matches our v75 sizing of the UVD BO (3168 KB rounded up
from 3.1 MB). So memory cost is unchanged relative to v75; we just
shift the binding to the GART side.

Expected:
  ✅ STATUS bit 1 sets — UVD initialized. Ring test passes.
  🟡 New behavior (different STATUS value, fault elsewhere) — fw
     advanced further; tells us what's missing next.
  ❌ Same STATUS=0x4 silent stall — regions not the gate; pivot to
     A5 (instrument) or A6 (retarget cache).

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
@@ -468,7 +468,12 @@
  * 0x300000000 to point at this BO instead of the dummy page. The VCPU
  * then reads its real firmware contents and (hopefully) executes.
  */
-#define PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE	0x1E0000UL		/* 1920 KB */
+#define PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE	0x1E0000UL		/* 1920 KB — firmware target */
+#define PS4_UVD_REGION2_SIZE	0x124000UL		/* 1168 KB — heap / IB stage */
+#define PS4_UVD_REGION3_SIZE	0x004000UL		/*   16 KB — message queue */
+#define PS4_UVD_REGIONS_TOTAL	(PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE + \
+				 PS4_UVD_REGION2_SIZE + \
+				 PS4_UVD_REGION3_SIZE)	/* 3.1 MB */
 #define PS4_UVD_FW_MIRROR_VA	0x300000000ULL		/* Sony's region 1 VA */

 static struct amdgpu_bo *uvd_fw_mirror_bo;
@@ -494,7 +499,7 @@
 	ucode_offset = le32_to_cpu(hdr->ucode_array_offset_bytes);
 	ucode_size = le32_to_cpu(hdr->ucode_size_bytes);

-	r = amdgpu_bo_create_kernel(adev, PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE,
+	r = amdgpu_bo_create_kernel(adev, PS4_UVD_REGIONS_TOTAL, PAGE_SIZE,
 				    AMDGPU_GEM_DOMAIN_GTT,
 				    &uvd_fw_mirror_bo,
 				    &mirror_gpu_addr,
@@ -505,21 +510,23 @@
 	}

 	/*
-	 * Zero out the whole region (Sony's region 1 includes a save/restore
-	 * area beyond the firmware text — leaving it zero matches what the
-	 * firmware would see on fresh allocation).
+	 * Zero out the whole 3-region area (Sony's region 1 has a save/restore
+	 * area beyond the firmware text, region 2 is heap/IB stage, region 3
+	 * is the message queue — all start zero on fresh allocation).
 	 */
-	memset(mirror_cpu_addr, 0, PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE);
-	/* Copy the firmware bytes into the start. */
+	memset(mirror_cpu_addr, 0, PS4_UVD_REGIONS_TOTAL);
+	/* Copy the firmware bytes into the start of region 1. */
 	memcpy(mirror_cpu_addr, adev->uvd.fw->data + ucode_offset, ucode_size);

 	/*
-	 * Rebind GART at 0x300000000 — overwrites the dummy bind from
-	 * gmc_v7_0_gart_enable (v76d-β-2-A) with the real firmware mirror
-	 * pages. The VC1..VC15 flat walk will now find real microcode/data
-	 * at this VA.
+	 * Rebind GART at 0x300000000 for the full 3-region span (3.1 MB).
+	 * Overwrites the dummy bind from gmc_v7_0_gart_enable (v76d-β-2-A).
+	 * The VC1..VC15 flat walk now finds:
+	 *   - 0x300000000..0x3001E0000 → firmware (region 1)
+	 *   - 0x3001E0000..0x300304000 → zeros   (region 2: heap/IB)
+	 *   - 0x300304000..0x300308000 → zeros   (region 3: msgq)
 	 */
-	num_pages = PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE / PAGE_SIZE;
+	num_pages = PS4_UVD_REGIONS_TOTAL / PAGE_SIZE;
 	amdgpu_gart_bind(adev, PS4_UVD_FW_MIRROR_VA, num_pages,
 			 uvd_fw_mirror_bo->tbo.ttm->dma_address,
 			 AMDGPU_PTE_VALID | AMDGPU_PTE_SYSTEM |
@@ -527,9 +534,9 @@
 	amdgpu_gart_invalidate_tlb(adev);

 	DRM_INFO("ps4 uvd: bound fw mirror at GART virtual 0x%llx "
-		 "(BO gpu_addr=0x%llx, fw_size=%u, region1_size=%lu)\n",
+		 "(BO gpu_addr=0x%llx, fw_size=%u, total_regions=%lu, pages=%d)\n",
 		 PS4_UVD_FW_MIRROR_VA, mirror_gpu_addr,
-		 ucode_size, PS4_UVD_REGION1_SIZE);
+		 ucode_size, PS4_UVD_REGIONS_TOTAL, num_pages);

 	uvd_fw_mirror_done = true;
 	return 0;
